races.nyt_race_description: Georgia has become an unexpected question mark for President Trump, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. posing a strong challenge in a state that Democrats have not carried in a presidential election since 1992.
races.poll_display: Polls close at 7 p.m. Eastern time.
races.expectations_text: Officials have said it could take a couple of days for all mail ballots to be scanned and counted, but the secretary of state has said he expects the winners of most races to be announced by Wednesday.
